 The Iranian government is reportedly weighing an assassination attempt against the American ambassador to South Africa Lana Marks. JOHANNESBURG - Iran is dismissing a US report claiming it's behind a plot to assassinate US ambassador to South Africa, Lana Marks. Iran is labelling the accusation as propaganda aimed at tarnishing its global standing. Iran's Foreign Affairs Ministry says the report seems to have been custom-ordered and is clearly biased. READ:Â Iranian embassy rejects assassination plot reports It says Iran is a responsible member of the International Community which would not resort to those tactics. The country, in turn, accuses the Trump administration of being a rogue regime, ignoring diplomatic principles. Iran also repeated its warning that it's still pursuing international legal action against the US for the assassination of General Qassem Soleimani.